The paper deals with the Visual Question Answering (VQA) challenge, which involves using machine learning to answer questions about images. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also proposes a new co-attention model, which involves natural language processing (cs.CL) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper discusses generating human-readable reasons for its decision, which could fall under information retrieval (cs.IR).
